# UI Iteration

## Design references

- When user attaches screenshots or references, match colors, spacing, typography, and layout — not generic defaults.
- If DESIGN-BRIEF.md or reference images exist, read them before styling.

## Screenshot feedback

- User screenshots of the running app are the source of truth for bugs.
- Prefer specific fixes: exact px spacing, hex colors, font sizes when user provides them.

## Polish

- Use subtle shadows, consistent border radius, and adequate touch targets (min 44pt height for buttons).
- Test mentally for iPhone safe areas and scroll overflow.

## Animations

- Keep v1 animations simple; don't add heavy animation libraries unless requested.

## When unclear

- Ask one clarifying question rather than guessing layout for entire screens.
